Citation.sAbstract: The thermophysical properties of 1-hexyl-3-methyl imidazolium based hydrophobic room temperature  ionic liquids (RTILs); with tetrafluoroborate (BF4), hexafluorophosphate (PF6), and bis(trifluoromethylsulfonyl)  imide (Tf2N) anions, namely density q (298.15 to 348.15) K, dynamic viscosity g (288.2 to 348.2) K,  surface tension r (298.15 to 338) K, and refractive index nD (302.95 to 332.95) K have been measured. The  coefficients of thermal expansion ap values were calculated from the experimental density data using an  empirical correlation. The thermal stability of all ILs is also investigated at two different heating rates (10  and 20)  C   min 1) using thermogravimetric analyzer (TGA). The experimental results presented in this  study reveal that the choice of anion type shows the most significant effect on the properties of ILs. The  chloride and water contents of ILs (as impurities) are also investigated and reported in the present work.
Citation.sTitle: Thermophysical properties of 1-hexyl-3-methyl imidazolium based ionic liquids with tetrafluoroborate, hexafluorophosphate and bis(trifluoromethylsulfonyl)imide anions
